# Project Context
This is a Next.js 16 RAG-based AI College Assistant where college 
authorities upload documents and students ask questions and get 
answers in their preferred language with Indian voice output.

# Who Uses What
- Authorities → upload documents (notices, syllabus, timetables, results)
- Students → ask questions via text or voice, get answers in their language

# Stack
- Frontend: Next.js 16 App Router with i18n (/en, /hi, /bn routing)
- Database: Supabase with pgvector (documents table, vector(768))
- AI: Google Gemini API (gemini-1.5-flash for chat, text-embedding-004 for embeddings)
- Voice: Web Speech API or Google TTS with Indian accent
- Embedding dimensions: 768

# Language Rules
- App supports English, Hindi, Bengali
- AI must detect the language of the student's question
- AI must always reply in the same language the student used
- Voice output must use Indian English accent or native language voice
- Never respond in a language the student did not use

# Coding Rules
- Use functional React components with hooks only
- All API routes go in: src/app/api/
- All database queries go in: src/lib/rag/
- Always handle errors in try/catch blocks
- Always show loading states when fetching data
- Never modify files outside of the task scope
- Use TypeScript everywhere, no any types

# Project Folder Structure
- src/app/api/chat/route.ts → RAG chat endpoint
- src/app/api/vector/ingest/route.ts → document ingestion endpoint
- src/app/api/upload/route.ts → file upload handler (to be built)
- src/app/api/voice/route.ts → voice/TTS handler (to be built)
- src/lib/rag/embeddings.ts → Gemini embedding functions
- src/lib/rag/supabase.ts → Supabase vector search client

# Commands
- Install packages: npm install [package]
- Run dev server: npm run dev
- Dev server runs on: http://localhost:3000

# Do NOT
- Never use inline styles
- Never use var (use const or let only)
- Never commit .env files
- Never change files not mentioned in the task
- Never add authentication for students
- Never use non-Indian accents for voice
- Never respond in a language the student did not use
- Never install new packages without asking first